<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002551.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Shadyjoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I'm now at a level where casters can do some serious damage in a hurry.  A green wizzie in Sol A burned 3 bubbles off me in 20 seconds last night (about 600 hps).  I guess I have to take these guys seriously.  Right now I'm using an exe axe for 100% of my fights, along with slam.  (Still trying to get one-handers better than langseaxes.)<P>I no longer just mash mash mash the slam key, I try to time it when I see the fire coming out of their hands.  Whenever I connect with slam, I interrupt them.  Fantastic.  But even with haste the slam goes too slow to catch all of their spells.<P>Any suggestions on some better tactics against these casting nasties?  I had heard that two gnoll hide lariats along with slam would be a great combo...  but the low damage on the lariats makes me wonder.<P>------------------<BR>.:Shady:.<P>[This message has been edited by Shadyjoe (edited February 23, 2000).]<p>[This message has been edited by Shadyjoe (edited February 23, 2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Bugbok</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I too have noticed that my slam does not refresh fast enough to interrupt some of the casters (e.g. Greater Ice Bones)  Instead of relying on the Mob's casting emotes, I usually slam as soon as I see "X begins to cast a spell"<P>Often times when I am soloing (e.g. pyramid in Cazic) where there are casters that can also heal, I will save my last few slams to interupt their heals instead of wasting them on the nukes.  I personally would rather get nuked and hope that I resist it then have the Mob heal back 2/3 of its life.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Oorgar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Another thing to mention...<P>if you're pulling for a group, and there's a wall nearby you can run behind (near the group) then get out of sight.  Casters will run to you till they can see you and you're in spell range.  Then the let it all out.  If you can round a corner they'll run right to you.<P>As for weapons to interupt them...  I dunno, bash is the only thing that really works for me.  Two langs just don't do it, neither does an SBH.<P>Oorgar<P>------------------<BR><B>Grumbo</B> &lt;The Hand of Evil&gt;<BR>Troll Warrior<I> Rallos Zek </I><BR><B>Faoldubh</B> &lt;The Hand of Evil&gt;<BR>Walking Gnome Lich <I>Rallos Zek</I><P>"Now go away or I shall taunt you a second time!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Shalindrea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">For npc only bash works but when dueling a pc use very fast weapons, they will have a good chance to interrupt as well as a shield if you are not a large race. With enough skill you will rarely loose a duel vs a caster (especially if you equip a lot of sv magic items too) unless of course they use a pet.<P><BR>Aelora, lvl 49 dark elf warrior</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Immudan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I used to try to slam as soon as I saw the pretty lights lighting up around a mob.  That's too late to be consistent.  Slam as soon as you see the message that the mob has begun casting and you'll interupt every time assuming your bash connects.<P>At high level there is approximately zero chance that a weapon hit will interrupt a mob's casting.  Only bash and stuns from spells will interrupt.  The lariot sounds cool because of the stun, but the damage is so pathetic that you will not be able to taunt anything.  Someone in my guild used a couple of these for awhile and came to the conclusion that they just don't do enough damage to be useable.  If they were 6/20 instead of 3/20 they'd be cool.<P>------------------<BR>Khumak - 47 Ogre Warrior<BR>Hasima - 8 Dark Elf Necro<BR>Immudan - 11 Erudite Wizard<BR>(Rodcet Nife)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Caper</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Shalindrea the big problem with pets is they don't zone.  For a duel that's no problem but in PvP that's such a big disadvantage that for PKing most casters don't even summon them.<P>Another cool thing to do against pets is NOT to hit them and train them to some gruesome monster.  If you haven't hit them then they'll aggro on the nice convenient Hill Giant.  And when the HG is done with the pet he'll take off after the caster.  You have an instant ally.<P>Caper the Hugely Happy Gemchopper<BR>Level 13 Warrior Vallon Zek.<P>P.S.  I wish Magic Resistance were enough!  A necro jumped me the other night and even though my MR was at 61 (not bad for a level 13) he still got me because of all the poison and disease spells.   <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/tongue.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Bushka</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">ermm lariats...me at lvl 46 uses dis sometimes the stun rocks and in conjunction with a ykesha i taunt fantastically...sadly fer me it seems to be that the speed at which you hit is what matters, i get damaged the bulk of the time in frenzy if the players im with are my lvl or just below or just above usin that thing, is rather annoying. Of course i have augment on so basically with my lvl bonus and that thing in my primary hand im hitting pretty much like a spam masheen.  Hmmm havnt used it while grouped with a monk or a waarrior an 2 ykeshas yet and to be honest i doubt it would work then.  But when yer with paladins and sk's low dly stuff works a treat.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
